{"id":22,"date":"2025-03-27T10:56:03","date_gmt":"2025-03-27T10:56:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/?p=22"},"modified":"2025-03-27T10:59:15","modified_gmt":"2025-03-27T10:59:15","slug":"grilled-snake-with-garlic-butter-and-herbs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/2025\/03\/27\/grilled-snake-with-garlic-butter-and-herbs\/","title":{"rendered":"Grilled Snake with Garlic Butter and Herbs"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This grilled snake recipe infuses the meat with smoky flavors, complemented by a rich garlic butter sauce and aromatic herbs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Ingredients<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>2 lbs snake meat (rattlesnake or python)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>3 tbsp olive oil<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>4 cloves garlic (minced)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp unsalted butter<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp smoked paprika<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp salt<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd tsp black pepper<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd tsp cayenne pepper (optional)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp dried oregano<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp dried thyme<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp fresh parsley (chopped)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 lemon (juiced)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp honey<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp soy sauce<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tbsp Dijon mustard<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Metal or wooden skewers (if using wooden skewers, soak them in water for 30 minutes)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Instructions<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Preparing the Snake Meat<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>If using a whole snake, skin and clean it properly. Remove the entrails, then cut it into 4\u20135-inch sections.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rinse the snake meat under cold water and pat it dry with paper towels.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, honey, mustard, salt, black pepper, paprika, oregano, and thyme.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Marinating<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Place the snake meat in the marinade and ensure it is fully coated.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours (preferably overnight for maximum flavor).<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Preparing the Grill<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lightly oil the grates to prevent sticking.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Grilling the Snake<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Skewer the meat pieces, or place them directly on the grill.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grill for 8\u201312 minutes, flipping occasionally, until the meat is opaque and firm.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 5: Making the Garlic Butter Sauce<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In a small pan, melt the butter over low heat.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add the minced garlic and saut\u00e9 until fragrant.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Remove from heat and mix in the parsley.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 6: Serving<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Brush the grilled snake with the garlic butter sauce.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Serve with grilled vegetables, rice, or fresh salad.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This grilled snake recipe infuses the meat with smoky flavors, complemented by a rich garlic butter sauce and aromatic herbs. Ingredients Instructions Step 1: Preparing [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":23,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-22","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-appetizers-snacks"],"_links"